text: St. Francis County is a county of the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2020 census, the population was 23,090. The county seat is Forrest City. The county was founded on October 13, 1827, and named for the St. Francis River. == References == Category:1820s establishments in Arkansas Territory Category:1827 establishments in the United States Category:Arkansas counties
title: St. Francis County, Arkansas
